Sony Considers $1 Billion Bid for All3Media, Telegraph Says

-- B y   Z i j i n g   W u
-- 
2011-05-01T07:38:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-01/sony-considers-1-billion-bid-for-all3media-telegraph-says.html
Sony Corp. (6758)  may consider a bid of more
than 600 million pounds ($1 billion) for All3Media Worldwide
Ltd., the U.K. television production company owned by Permira
Advisers LLP, according to the Sunday Telegraph.  Sony Pictures Television, the Japanese electronics maker’s
TV unit, is keen to expand its presence in the U.K., the
newspaper said, citing unidentified people familiar with the
matter.  Time Warner Inc. (TWX)  may also bid for All3Media, the Sunday
Telegraph said. Both Sony and Time Warner’s interest are still
“very early stage,” according to the report.  -- Editors:  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zijing Wu in London at   zwu17@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jeff St.Onge at   jstonge@bloomberg.net . 